briefdescription.para: Function to create a one-dimensional interpolator.

detaileddescription.para:
Function to create a one-dimensional interpolator from the data that is to be interpolated, as well as the settings that are to be used to create the interpolator.
dataToInterpolate
Map providing data that is to be interpolated (key = independent variables, value = dependent variables).
interpolatorSettings
Settings that are to be used to create interpolator.
defaultExtrapolationValue
Pair of default values to be used for extrapolation, in case of use_default_value or use_default_value_with_warning as methods for boundaryHandling.
firstDerivativeOfDependentVariables
First derivative of dependent variables w.r.t. independent variable at independent variables values in values of dataToInterpolate. By default, this vector is empty, it only needs to be supplied if the selected interpolator requires this data (e.g. Hermite spline).
Interpolator created from dataToInterpolate using interpolatorSettings.

memberdef.name: solveTridiagonalMatrixEquation

detaileddescription.para:
This functions efficiently solves the matrix equation Ax = b for b, where A is tri-diagonal. The required input are the diagonal and sub/super diagonals of A, as well as the vector b. Input is given as STL vectors. The input diagonals must be at least the same size as right-hand-side. Any additional entries (at end) will be ignored in the algorithm.
IndependentVariableType
Type of independent variables.
DependentVariableType
Type of dependent variables.
subDiagonal
Sub-diagonal of matrix A.
superDiagonal
Super-diagonal of matrix A.
diagonal
Diagonal of matrix A.
rightHandSide
Right-hand-side of matrix equation.
Solution to matrix equation.

memberdef.name: computeLinearInterpolation

detaileddescription.para:
Computes linear interpolation of data provided in the form of a vector of sorted indepedent variables and an associated vector of dependent variables. The linear interpolation equation used is: \[ y_{target} = x_{1} * ( 1 - mu ) + x_{2} * mu \] where $ mu = \frac{ x_{target} - x_{1} } { x_{2} + x_{1} } $ and $ x_{2} > x_{1} $.
sortedIndependentVariables
Vector of independent variables sorted. in ascending/descending order.
associatedDependentVariables
Vector of dependent variables associated with sorted vector of independent variables.
targetIndependentVariableValue
Target independent variable value in vector of sorted independent variables.
Value of dependent variable associated with target independent value in vector of sorted independent variables.

memberdef.name: computeLinearInterpolation

detaileddescription.para:
Computes linear interpolation of data provided in the form of a map of independent variables and associated vectors of dependent variables. The linear interpolation equation used is: \[ y_{target} = x_{1} * ( 1 - mu ) + x_{2} * mu \] where $ \mu = \frac{ x_{target} - x_{1} } { x_{2} + x_{1} } $ and $ x_{2} > x_{1} $.
sortedIndepedentAndDependentVariables
Map of sorted independent variables, in ascending/descending order, and associated dependent variables.
targetIndependentVariableValue
Target independent variable value in vector of sorted independent variables.
Vector of dependent variable associated with target independent value in vector of sorted independent variables.
